        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 12:01AM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 1200 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles southwest of 4 Bears Lodge, or 30 miles southwest of Stanley,
moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
New Town, Mandaree, Van Hook Park, 4 Bears Lodge, Belden, Four Bears
Village, Pouch Point Recreation Area, Crow Flies High State
Recreation Area, Parshall Bay Recreation Area, and Fort Berthold.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for
south central, southwestern and northwestern North Dakota.</instruction>
